      • rank

        public boolean rank(java.lang.Double d,
                    java.lang.Integer iter,
                    java.lang.Double tol)
        Performs PageRank algorithm over linkFile and saves results to scoreFile with the stop conditions passed as argument. Non verbose mode by default.
        Parameters:
        d - bias value for the algorithm.
        iter - max number of iterations.
        tol - threshold, once rank values don't change more than this value
        from one iteration to another, the algorithm will stop.
        Returns:
        true if everything went OK. false on error.

      • rank

        public boolean rank(java.lang.Double d,
                    java.lang.Integer iter,
                    java.lang.Double tol,
                    boolean verbose)
        Performs PageRank algorithm over linkFile and saves results to scoreFile with the stop conditions passed as argument.
        Parameters:
        d - bias value for the algorithm.
        iter - max number of iterations.
        tol - threshold, once rank values don't change more than this value
        from one iteration to another, the algorithm will stop.
        verbose - prints the value of rank vector on each iteration
        Returns:
        true if everything went OK. false on error.
